00:17:22,771 --> 00:17:26,692
And not only we don't remember everything, and for what we

366
00:17:26,692 --> 00:17:28,053
remember, it's not accurate.

367
00:17:28,705 --> 00:17:31,127
And we also have false memories.

368
00:17:31,127 --> 00:17:31,787
It's a mess.

369
00:17:31,787 --> 00:17:35,049
We can't really rely on the memories.

370
00:17:35,049 --> 00:17:38,731
And that's a problem, because a game is an experience that we

371
00:17:38,731 --> 00:17:43,253
have over several days, weeks, hopefully months and years.

372
00:17:43,253 --> 00:17:45,375
So we want to make sure that from one day to the next,

373
00:17:45,375 --> 00:17:47,956
players are not going to forget about critical

374
00:17:47,956 --> 00:17:51,058
information from them to be successful playing the game.

375
00:17:52,360 --> 00:18:00,165
And a quick win about that is to make sure that we remove some memory load.

376
00:18:00,165 --> 00:18:03,186
So if you're not asking players to memorize something,

377
00:18:03,186 --> 00:18:04,467
then there's no problem.

378
00:18:04,467 --> 00:18:05,688
They're not going to forget about it

