532
00:25:34,495 --> 00:25:37,175
Extrinsic is when you do something

533
00:25:37,175 --> 00:25:39,056
to get something else.

534
00:25:39,056 --> 00:25:41,717
Intrinsic is when you do it for the sake of it.

535
00:25:41,717 --> 00:25:43,438
So that's really important to try

536
00:25:43,438 --> 00:25:46,619
to make sure that your players have what

537
00:25:46,619 --> 00:25:50,000
they need to be motivated intrinsically and extrinsically.

538
00:25:50,382 --> 00:25:54,703
And then whenever, when it's intrinsic, there's a meaning,

539
00:25:54,703 --> 00:25:57,444
and when they have to do something intrinsically,

540
00:25:57,444 --> 00:26:00,005
so it's competence, autonomy, relateness,

541
00:26:00,005 --> 00:26:02,786
it's also meaningful to what they're trying to accomplish.

542
00:26:02,786 --> 00:26:05,266
And then when you survey your players,

543
00:26:05,266 --> 00:26:08,847
you can use that to try to find out,

544
00:26:08,847 --> 00:26:11,128
you know, if players get the purpose

545
00:26:11,128 --> 00:26:13,248
and the objectives of what they have to do,

546
00:26:13,248 --> 00:26:15,269
and if it's meaningful to them.

547
00:26:15,269 --> 00:26:17,770
So this is when you can use Likert scales,

548
00:26:17,770 --> 00:26:18,750
Likert scales like this,

549
00:26:18,750 --> 00:26:19,150
and try to...

550
00:26:20,217 --> 00:26:25,522
figure out what's going on and if they understand what they need to do in the game.

551
00:26:25,522 --> 00:26:26,423
And later on with analytics.

552
00:26:26,423 --> 00:26:33,469
So that's, you know, the ingredients that we can use, the rules of thumb that help us out,

553
00:26:33,469 --> 00:26:35,591
but it's also establishing a common language.

554
00:26:35,591 --> 00:26:36,512
It's really important.

555
00:26:36,512 --> 00:26:42,597
That's important, the QA also knows about it, so they can reference back to it from time to time.

556
00:26:43,888 --> 00:26:46,130
And the last step is process.

557
00:26:46,130 --> 00:26:51,554
So establishing a process, especially around UX testing,

558
00:26:51,554 --> 00:26:53,436
make sure that we start with hypotheses.

559
00:26:53,436 --> 00:26:55,957
We're not just doing UX test for UX test, that the

560
00:26:55,957 --> 00:26:57,899
developers participate in it.

561
00:26:57,899 --> 00:26:58,800
We have a plan.

562
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:00,121
We have goals.

563
00:27:00,121 --> 00:27:03,443
We test a build that QA knows what to look for.

564
00:27:03,443 --> 00:27:05,545
It doesn't know what we're going to test.

565
00:27:05,545 --> 00:27:07,706
So they're going to ensure there's no bugs for these

566
00:27:07,706 --> 00:27:09,968
particular features or systems.

